<<<
''Displays analog and digital clocks with automatic update.''
<br>Requires: [[TiddlyTools/Time/Ticker]], [[TiddlyTools/Time/action-timeout.js]]
<br>Optional: [[TiddlyTools/Time/Setup]], <$link to=<<tt_time_config>>/>

* By default, the clocks show the local time.
* To display both clocks, use `{{TiddlyTools/Time/Clocks}}`
* To display either clock separately, use `<<clock type:"analog">>` or `<<clock type:"digital">>`.
* You can set the time format for the digital clock and the styles used by the analog clock (see [[TiddlyTools/Time/Setup]] or <$link to=<<tt_time_config>>/>).
* To override the format for a specific digital clock instance, add `format:"..."` to the macro parameters, where the text of the format uses [[TiddlyWiki Date Format codes|https://tiddlywiki.com/#DateFormat]].
* To specify a different timezone, add `offset:"..."` to the macro parameters, with a value of `-12:00` through `+12:00`, where the number is the hours and minutes offset from [[UTC|https://www.timeanddate.com/time/aboututc.html]].
