!! [[TiddlyTools/Time/Places]]
<<<
''Contains a set of places and timezone offsets used by [[TiddlyTools/Time/WorldClocks]]''
<br>Optional: [[TiddlyTools/Time/Places/Summer]]

@@.resize
* Press <<button {{$:/core/images/edit-button}} tc-btn-invisible>> in [[TiddlyTools/Time/WorldClocks]] to add/remove places in the current set.
* Enter place names and [[timezone offsets|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_UTC_time_offsets]], one place name and timezone offset per line.
* Separate the place names and the timezone offsets using a colon (:). Leading and trailing "whitespace" are ignored.
* Enter timezone offsets using `-12:00` through `+12:00`, where the number is the hours and minutes offset from [[UTC|https://www.timeanddate.com/time/aboututc.html]].
* Note: some places (but not all) change timezone offsets for spring/summer months (Daylight Saving Time).
** A separate tiddler, [[TiddlyTools/Time/Places/Summer]], contains alternative timezone offsets for spring/summer months.

You can also ''create your own tiddler(s) containing additional custom sets of places and timezone offsets'':

* Press <<button {{$:/core/images/clone-button}} tc-btn-invisible>> in [[TiddlyTools/Time/WorldClocks]] to copy the selected individual places to a new set.
* The __title__ of the new tiddler can be anything you want, as long as the tiddler is tagged with <<tag places>>.
* Edit the __text__ field to add/remove places and timezone offsets as described above.
* The __caption__ field should contain a suitably distinct description for your custom set of places.  If the __caption__ field is removed or left blank, the tiddler's title will be used.
